# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this React + Vite project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 using npm
- Package added to dependencies in `package.json`

### 2. Analytics Integration
**Modified: `src/main.jsx`**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component to the root React render output
- Wrapped the App component and Analytics in a React Fragment to maintain proper structure

### 3. Files Updated
- `frontend/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `frontend/package-lock.json` - Updated with new package dependencies
- `frontend/src/main.jsx` - Integrated Analytics component

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics quickstart documentation (fetched on 2026-04-11), the Analytics component was added to the root of the application in `main.jsx`. This is the recommended approach for React/Vite projects.

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and web vitals when the application is deployed to Vercel. No additional configuration is required for basic analytics tracking.

## Verification

✅ Build completed successfully - no errors introduced
✅ Package installed correctly with npm
✅ Lock file updated properly
✅ Code structure preserved - only necessary changes made
✅ Analytics component properly integrated at application root

## Next Steps

To activate analytics tracking:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the Analytics section in the Vercel dashboard
3. Click "Enable" to start tracking
4. Analytics data will begin appearing after deployment

The analytics will track page views, web vitals (CLS, FID, FCP, LCP, TTFB), and other user interaction metrics automatically.
